snippet.textDisplay: Ok here my explanation: Soyeon is a fallen angel, who was punished by the Goddess (Miyeon). She is now in hell, but has enough power to escape from hell, one can day that she is Lucifer or Satan. She is in the same white room as Minnie in the beginning, she tries to influence Minnie to leave "heaven" and follow her to hell. Minnie has already big doubts about her religion or her Goddess, who is Miyeon. She starts looking for answers in the white room, she sees some curtains and open them. It is another green room, one can see Yuqi, it is like a long corridor and there are many different rooms, which lead to heaven where Miyeon (The goddess) is and hell, where Soyeon (the devil) is. One can say that Yuqi is between hell and heaven because she can see both sides and when she sees the goddess, she is shocked and Miyeon notices her and sends Yuqi to hell as a punishment. Why? Miyeon is actually a bad goddess, as the lyrics say she is beautiful but evil inside, there are also several people with her in Miyeons room, these are also souls or humans, which were sent to hell. Soojin is also a fallen angel, who was sent to hell and she sees Shuhua. Shuhua has also a high position in heaven, she is the legal representative of Miyeon ( in South Korea, purple implies the image of somebody who delivers the words of god). Shuhua is following Miyeon's rules, but Soojin appears in front of Shuhua and tells her the truth about Miyeon, who is actually evil. Shuhua decides to go to hell with Soojin. In the end Minnie is also in hell because she found the truth about Miyeon. Everyone was sent to hell because of their doubts, Miyeon wants nobody to know about her real self, so she sends everybody to hell, who has doubts or sees her true self. Shuhua was the only one who went to hell voluntarily because Soojin told her about Miyeons true self. In the end Soyeon's plan succeed because Minnie is in hell now and found the truth about her doubts.
